commit.message:
Fix some broken links:

- git repo now on github
- news link died a long time ago
Type and prototype fixes.
More type cleanup.
Compiler warnings are not helping here.
Fix some types & prototypes.

Clean up some dead code from 1cace3ad.

Also fix some types.
Make the inner loop clearer still.
Reorganise inner loop for rsync algorithm.
Pull out z->context references from inner loop.
Test for block adler32.

Optimise adler32 in rcksum_calc_rsum_block.

* Additive calculation of adler32.
* Use indexing and int-sized len in rcksum_calc_rsum_block for 30% speedup.
Report blocksize and .zsync size.

New tuning for hash lengths, tidy up.

* prefer seq_matches=1, since the continuation matching seems flawed (poor
  performance in some cases).
* use ceil() consistently instead of +7.9 stuff.
* min and max bounds for # of bytes for hash lengths.
New regression test scripts.

Old regression test script.

Bring into version control for historical reference.

Fix a loop caused by incorrect remote data.

The client is supposed to notice if the remote gives it bad data (inconsistent
with the .zsync) and stop using that URL. But there was an edge case where it
would not spot the error and would re-download the same byte range
indefinitely. Thanks Gian Merlino.
We're going to need a bigger hashhit.
Bump version #.
Bump version #.
Use e pointer instead of looking up by id.
Move min, max to common header; more diagnostics.
Fix previous commit - hash function was not making good use of the bitspace, causing a performance regression.
Allow hash table to be as large as is needed to achieve a good load factor.
Add NEWS entry for previous commits.
Fancier progress monitoring - keep history over 10s now.

Better progress indication for local seed data.

Overhaul progress code.
Report stats on how densely filled the hash tables in librcksum are.

Add --enable-debug to enable the DEBUG flag.

This turns on some stats in librcksum.
Privacy notice, adsense.

Improve messages and download error handling.

Download errors were sometimes not noticed by the main program, so it would proceed to verifying the download although it was incomplete and give inappropriate messages. I have rearranged things so it checks zsync_status itself.
Also improvements to many of the progress and error messages given, based on feedback.
